description.narrative: UNICEF contributed inputs to improve the education quality. However, learning outcomes remain low – according to MICS, 7 per cent of children 7-14 years old, schooled or not, have basic competencies in math and 23 per cent in reading. This weak relationship might be due to (a) insufficient time for positive impacts; (b) pertinence of the inputs; (c) inadequate delivery. Unfortunately, there is no clear evidence on either of these hypotheses or on the indirect and confounding effects of the inputs. Until greater insight is achieved, the output is constrained. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:31/12/2019
